# Local only — copy to `.env` and fill in (never commit `.env`).
# Client Firebase config (VITE_* is embedded in the production JS bundle; restrict keys in Google Cloud).
# Gemini stays on the server: use `server/.env` with GEMINI_API_KEY.
#
# Auth checklist (Firebase Console → Authentication):
# - Enable Email/Password and (optionally) Google.
# - Templates: ensure “Email address verification” and “Password reset” are enabled; links use your authorized domain.
# - Settings → Authorized domains: include localhost, 127.0.0.1, and your production host (hostname only; ports use the same host entry).
# - Email/password users must verify before the app unlocks. Verification links use handleCodeInApp=false (standard web); if you see
#   “unauthorized-continue-uri”, add this exact site origin’s host under Authorized domains.

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=
# Use (default) unless you created a named Firestore database
VITE_FIREBASE_FIRESTORE_DATABASE_ID=(default)

# Production and native (Capacitor): public HTTPS origin of the Express API (no trailing slash).
# Omit for local web dev — Vite proxies /api → http://127.0.0.1:8787 (see vite.config.ts).
# The bundled app cannot use that proxy; mobile builds must set this to your deployed API.
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.your-domain.com
#
# Server CORS: list this web app’s hosting origin(s) plus Capacitor origins, e.g. in server/.env:
# CORS_ORIGIN=https://regrade.web.app,https://regrade.firebaseapp.com,capacitor://localhost,ionic://localhost
